TOPIC 1: TIME SPEEDING UP & LIVING IN THE MOMENT

The Question

• Things seem to be coming faster in life
• Good things are happening
• Is it just belief or is time actually speeding up?

Bashar's Explanation: Creating Less Time

• When you live more in the moment, you actually CREATE LESS TIME
• So it seems in your terms to be speeding up, but that's because you're actually creating less of it
• You're jumping over - making bigger jumps (analogy)

Living in the Moment Allows You to Experience

• There actually IS only one moment: NOW
• What you call another moment is actually THE SAME MOMENT from a different point of view
• The more you live in the moment:
  - The less details you create
  - The more integrated you are
  - The more holistic you are

The Relationship Between Holistic Being and Time

• The more holistic you are, the less details you need
• The less time you need
• The ONLY reason you need more time is when you start compartmentalizing and fragmenting yourself into many more details than is necessary

Creating More Details Creates More Time

• When you create more details, more steps:
  - Need to do this, need to do that
  - A, B, C, D, E, F, G
  - Then you need to create more time in which those details can exist

Going From A to Z

• When you can go A to Z (because you know it's the same moment)
• Then you don't need as much time
• Time from a physical point of view will then seem to speed up

